               <floruit when="1555">He was  the sixth abbot of the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC3653GundaG">Gunda Gunde</placeName>
                  and became an abbot  in <date>1555</date> succeeding ʾabbā 
                  <persName ref="PRS9192TaklaNa">Takla Nabiyāt</persName>. 
                  He was a relative of  
                  <persName ref="PRS3894estifano"><roleName type="title">ʾabbā </roleName> ʾƎsṭifānos</persName>, the first leader of <persName ref="PRS11211Stephanites">Stephanites</persName>.
                  He took the monastic habit at the age of 15 from the hands of <persName ref="PRS4322GabraMa">Gabra Maśiḥ</persName>. He was represented in the community as an interpreter of the Scriptures.
                  </floruit>
                  <death> He died in <date>1572</date>
